Chapter.Heading: Small LeibnizAlgebra Package
Chapter.Section:
Accessing Small LeibnizAlgebra AllSmallLeibnizAlgebra is an accessor function for accessing the complete list of non-isomorphic leibnizalgebra models from orders 2 to 4.
The models are generated by Mace4 , using the definitions in Section .

Definition of LeibnizAlgebra formulas(LeibnizAlgebra).
x+(y+z)=(x+y)+z.
x+y=y+x.
x+0=0+x.
x+f(x)=0.
a(x+y,z)=a(x,z)+a(y,z).
a(x,y+z)=a(x,y)+a(x,z).
a(a(x,y),z) = a(a(x,z),y) + a(x,a(y,z)).
end_of_list.
Dependency This package has no dependencies .
